		<p>I'm a 32 years old IT Project Manager who is currently unemployed. I was born in Israel and lived in New Zealand for the past 7 years. A few weeks ago I decided to go back to Israel for an extended holiday.</p>
		
		<p>I worked in the IT industry for approx. 15 years. I started off as a computer technician in 1996 and in 2000 became a software developer. I moved to New Zealand in 2004 and in 2006 started my own software development company based in Wellington. I started managing software projects for internal projects and in 2007 I started providing project management services to a wider group of clients in the Wellington region.</p>
		
